author: @user-dj9jw9uz9p
text: Don't launch web apps from Idle. Either use a command line, so you can just kill it with Ctrl-C (or Ctrl-Break) or an IDE like PyDev or PyCharm. Idle is pretty cool baby's first editor, but it's not really suitable for a serious development, especially if you're developing web apps or daemons or services or stuff like that.

author: @nektoxyz1013
text: 2 @sentdex:  Man sorry for posting it here. But i cant see how much pain it gains to you to stop DASH server. My personal approach to stop server, in the line as follows: app.run_server(debug  = True),  i make a mistake, and save it, (delete first letter for example) The server get an error, and stops automatically. You have no need to kill the ptyhon process. Correct code, and reprint first letter. Saves  a lot of time. Best Regards. Alex.
